column2: Area has had about 2 weeks of 80-90 degree temps.  Many suspended lake bed nutrients noticeable believe from heavy boating use.  The lake needs a staff gauge to monitor water levels.  Old high water mark cannot be found.
Very calm wind- 80 degrees- clear skies.  Sunny- little or no algal blooms.
Floating zooplankton would like to identify.
Very little sight of algal blooms. Sawyer nestled within a shoreline of large trees not normally real windy but not ( ) .
70 degrees- hazy- light wind- heavy fishing activity. Suspended zooplankton noticeable top 5'.
Mayfly hatch last night.  Tree fuzz on surface.  Air temperature 72 degrees- water temperature 69 degrees.
Saw 2 loons on water + 2 eagles flying.
Light SW wind- sunny.  Water temp 72 deg F.
No boat activity- purple loosestrife increasing - send beetles- 75 F air temp.
75 F air temp- no boat activity- breezy- sunshine- no clouds.
70 F- no boat activity- breezy- sunshine- no clouds.
No other boat activity- calm and sunny day- mid 60s- saw an eagle.  Saw an oriole in a tree.
1 fishing boat. Calm and sunny day- mid 70 degrees.
Calm and sunny- 80 degrees- no boat activity.
Two fishing boats and one canoe- 70 degrees- overcast with sun occasionally- light breeze.
No boat activity.  Breezy and sunny.  Very quiet.  Saw an eagle soaring over lake.
70 degrees- sunny and breezy. No boat activity.
Sunny- windy- the temperature is 72 degrees- and there are four boats - three are fishing.
Sunny with a light breeze- the temperature is 80 degrees- and there is one fishing boat and several canoeist.
Sunny with a light breeze- the temperature is 73 degrees- it is quiet- and there are two boats- a canoe- and a kayak.
Sunny; 73 degrees; light breeze; one fishing boat.
2 eagles soaring 2 young in nest- secchi disc smaller secton of lake 16'- mostly cloudy day
2 loons- 2 adult eagles with 2 young- deep hole smaller section of lake secchi reading 17'- sunny day
2 young eagles at nest- secchi reading smaller section of lake 16'6". sunny day
1 loon- secchi reading smaller section of lake 16'6" - overcast
secchi reading smaller section of lake 17'0"- overcast
62 degrees. Cloudy- south wind approximately 5 MPH. Slight chop. No power boats.
72 degrees. Water temperature on surface - 70.8 degrees F.
76.7 degrees F on surface of water.
Calm wind. Cloudy. 70 degrees surface temperature.

65.7 deg surface temp- SxSW wind 0-15 mph- sunny and hazy w thin clouds 65.7 deg surface temp- SxSW wind 0-15 mph- sunny and hazy w thin clouds. 2 loons present. Greenish clear w suspended zooplankton. Green clumps of algae on windward side of lake? To pick-up-(?) help- get sample. No boats except camp boat touring.
Calm and sunny- mid 70s. 31' bottom. Lots of algae floating. Suspended zooplankton exct.
67 deg. Clear- slight chop- no algae seen
A green color of something from the trees floating on the surface on windward shoreline out 2' to 3' from the shore
Springs noticeable in 22' if water SE of deep hole. Sunny and 65 F- calm wind. No other boats in sight.
Cloudy- calm surface- no boat traffic. Two adult loons their young did not survive or eggs were destroyed.
